---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Notes - Cache Atlas">
  <main class="page">
    <div class="eyebrow">notes</div>
    <h1>Paper notes and implementation writeups.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      These notes track my learning process in public: one mechanism at a time, with enough implementation detail,
      visuals, and reproduction notes to make the code path inspectable.
    </p>

    <section class="toc">
      <ol>
        <li>
          <a href="/notes/why-kv-cache-papers-matter">Why KV cache papers matter</a>
          <p>The opening map of the memory problem behind modern inference serving.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="/notes/reproducing-minicache-in-pytorch">Reproducing MiniCache in PyTorch</a>
          <p>The first implementation report, centered on <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2405.14366" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">arXiv:2405.14366</a>.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="toc">
      <div class="label">categories</div>
      <ul class="category-list">
        <li>
          <strong>KV-cache memory</strong>
          <p>Cache footprint, decode bottlenecks, and compression strategies.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Implementation notes</strong>
          <p>Reproducible code paths with tests, examples, and benchmark commands.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="toc">
      <div class="label">next note</div>
      <p>
        Next up: PrefixKV, with the same standard: one mechanism, a small implementation boundary, and a clear
        reproduction path.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .toc {
    margin-top: 28px;
    padding-top: 18px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .toc ol {
    margin: 12px 0 0;
    padding-left: 20px;
  }

  .toc li {
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }

  .toc a {
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .toc p {
    margin: 6px 0 0;
  }
</style>
